The data shows quarterly revenue across four regions for a fiscal year with 11.4% overall year-over-year growth. North region led growth at 18.2% (from $142,500 to $195,400), while South showed the weakest performance at 4.3% with a Q3 dip to $95,700. East was the highest-revenue region throughout all quarters, reaching $267,800 in Q4. Total revenue grew steadily each quarter from $633,300 to $773,400.